    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-09-13T08:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-09-13T08:00:00-05:00" n="525"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d525">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 103.94/416</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="#p_PWH1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Page</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-09-13T14:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 13, 1918, 2 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 2.45 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1853. To <persName corresp="#p_BBM1">Baruch</persName> from <persName
                        corresp="#p_SLL1">Summers</persName>:</p>
                <p>Maritime Council requires by September 20:</p>
                <p>Approximate statement of amounts necessary to import, year commencing September
                    1, 1918, ending August 31, 1919. Also what, if any, shipping arranged for. State
                    consumption imports and exports, also stocks on hand, if possible, of each fiber
                    for year ending September 1, 1918, and ports of origin of imports for jute,
                    flax, hemp, sisal and similar fibers.</p>
                <p>An immediate answer imperative. <persName>Patterson</persName>.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_PWH1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Page</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
